  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Blind Adults that willing to participate in the study will be tested with well-established
      measuring techniques of Balance control using force plate in the movement and Rehabilitation
      Laboratory at Ben-Gurion University. An automated algorithm will be used to extract
      standardized stabilogram-diffusion parameters from each of the COP data sets collected during
      quiet standing. These parameters include diffusion coefficients, critical displacement,
      critical time and scaling exponents for both lateral and anterior-posterior sway directions
      (Collins &amp; De Luca, 1993). the subjects will be tested in 3 task conditions (eyes
      blindfolded, eyes blindfolded holding stick, eyes blindfolded holding a dog). Participants
      will be required to stand on the platform 10 times for 30 s For each trial, they will be
      instructed to sway as little as possible.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
